    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Northern California Coast</b> (263Ag, Al). Stands of <i>A. montana </i>have been sampled and mapped in Marin County (Evens and Kentner 2006, Buck-Diaz and Evens 2010, Buck-Diaz et. al 2021), and stands of <i>A. bakeri </i>have been sampled and mapped in Sonoma County (Klein et al. 2015).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Although locally numerous, stands are globally few and contain rare taxa in addition to <i>Arctostaphylos bakeri </i> and <i>A. montana. </i>Medium to long fire return intervals are important to maintain the alliance. Suburban development, invasive species, road construction and widening, trash dumping, and other impacts threaten the alliance, especially stands of <i>A. bakeri </i>ssp. <i>bakeri.</i> </div>
</div>

    

    

